trans-unit.source: Provides a typed class that represents a compiled XPath expression.
trans-unit.target: Inneholder en typeangitt klasse som representerer et kompilerte XPath-uttrykk.

trans-unit.source: This class is returned as the result of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Compile%2A> method of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> class.
trans-unit.target: Denne klassen returneres som et resultat av <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Compile%2A>metoden for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>klasse.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Compile%2A>

trans-unit.source: It is a parameter to the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Evaluate%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Matches%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Select%2A>, and <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SelectSingleNode%2A> methods of the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> class.
trans-unit.target: Det er en parameter i <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Evaluate%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Matches%2A>, <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Select%2A>, og <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SelectSingleNode%2A>metoder for <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator>klassen.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.SelectSingleNode%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Select%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Matches%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator.Evaluate%2A>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, sorts the nodes selected by the XPath expression according to the specified <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> object.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, sorterer noder som er valgt av XPath-uttrykk i henhold til den angitte <xref:System.Collections.IComparer>objektet.</xref:System.Collections.IComparer>

trans-unit.source: The AddSort method enables users to sort objects by their data type instead of by string or number.
trans-unit.target: Metoden AddSort gjør det mulig for brukere å sortere objekter av datatypen i stedet for i streng eller tall.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> object provides an implementation of the <xref:System.Collections.IComparer.Compare%2A> method that supports sorting on user-defined classes.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Collections.IComparer>-objektet har en implementering av den <xref:System.Collections.IComparer.Compare%2A>metoden som støtter sortering på brukerdefinerte klasser.</xref:System.Collections.IComparer.Compare%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IComparer>

trans-unit.source: In the following example, the books are sorted by ISBN number, where `isbn` is an object that implements the <xref:System.Collections.IComparer> interface.
trans-unit.target: I eksemplet nedenfor bøkene sortert etter ISBN tall, der `isbn` er et objekt som implementerer den <xref:System.Collections.IComparer>grensesnittet.</xref:System.Collections.IComparer>

trans-unit.source: ```vb# Dim expression As XPathExpression = navigator.Compile("bookstore/book") Dim isbn As ISBN = New ISBN() expression.AddSort("@ISBN", (IComparer)isbn) ``` ```c# XPathExpression expression = navigator.Compile("bookstore/book"); ISBN isbn = new ISBN(); expression.AddSort("@ISBN", (IComparer)isbn); ``` The following are important notes to consider when using the AddSort method.
trans-unit.target: ```vb# Dim expression As XPathExpression = navigator.Compile("bookstore/book") Dim isbn As ISBN = New ISBN() expression.AddSort("@ISBN", (IComparer)isbn) ``` ```c# XPathExpression expression = navigator.Compile("bookstore/book"); ISBN isbn = new ISBN(); expression.AddSort("@ISBN", (IComparer)isbn); ```Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker AddSort-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - The order in which the sorts are added provides the sort key order.
trans-unit.target: -Ordren sorteringene er lagt til gir sorteringen nøkkelkolonner rekkefølge.

trans-unit.source: - If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> or the sort key requires namespace resolution, you must use the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A> method to provide an <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> for namespace resolution.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>eller sorteringsnøkkelen krever navneområdet løsning, må du bruke den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A>metode for å angi en <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>for navneområdet oppløsning.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>

trans-unit.source: - If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> does not include a prefix, it is assumed that the namespace Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) is the empty namespace.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>inneholder ikke et prefiks antas det at navneområdet Uniform URI (Resource Identifier) er tomme navneområdet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>

trans-unit.source: If your XML includes a default namespace, you must still use the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A> method and provide an <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> that contains a prefix and namespace URI to handle the default namespace.
trans-unit.target: Hvis XML-filen inneholder et standard navneområde, må du fortsatt bruke den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A>metoden og angi en <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>som inneholder et prefiks og navneområde-URI til å håndtere standard navneområde.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > It is not possible to compile a <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> with a custom context in one step by passing an <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltContext>, which implements <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>, as an argument to this method.

trans-unit.source: Namespace resolution is supported using classes that implement the <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> interface, such as the <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> class.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> stores prefix and namespace Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) mappings.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>lagrer prefikset og navneområdet Uniform URI (Resource Identifier)-tilordninger.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> requires namespace resolution, the prefix and namespace URI pair must be added to an object, such as the <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> class, which implements the <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> interface, and the SetContext method must be called to specify the <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> interface object to use for namespace resolution.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>krever navneområdet oppløsning, prefikset og navneområdet URI-par må legge til et objekt som den <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>klasse som implementerer den <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>grensesnittet og SetContext-metoden må kalles for å angi den <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>objekt for klyngenettverksgrensesnitt skal brukes for navneområdet oppløsning.</xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> </xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> </xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the SetContext method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker SetContext-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> does not include a prefix, it is assumed that the namespace URI is the empty namespace.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>inneholder ikke et prefiks antas det at navneområde-URI er tom navneområdet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>

trans-unit.source: If your XML includes a default namespace, you must still use the SetContext method and provide an object that contains a prefix and namespace URI to handle the default namespace.
trans-unit.target: Hvis XML-filen inneholder et standard navneområde, må du fortsatt bruke metoden SetContext og angi et objekt som inneholder et prefiks og navneområde-URI til å håndtere standard navneområde.

trans-unit.source: - You can also supply an <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> interface object for namespace resolution to the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.Compile%2A> method when you create your <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> object.
trans-unit.target: -Du kan også angi en <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>objekt for klyngenettverksgrensesnitt for navneområdet løsningen til den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.Compile%2A>metoden når du oppretter din <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>objektet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.Compile%2A> </xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>

trans-unit.source: - SetContext accepts <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltContext> as a namespace resolver, so you can implement a custom context and use functions and variables based on <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextFunction> and <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextVariable>.
trans-unit.target: -SetContext godtar <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltContext>som et navneområde-Løsningsprogram, så du kan implementere en egendefinert kontekst og bruke funksjoner og variabler som er basert på <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextFunction>og <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextVariable>.</xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextVariable> </xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextFunction> </xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltContext>

trans-unit.source: An object that implements the <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> interface to use for namespace resolution.
trans-unit.target: Et objekt som implementerer den <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>grensesnitt som skal brukes for navneområdet oppløsning.</xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> object parameter is not derived from <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>Objekt-parameteren er ikke utledet fra <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>.</xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> </xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>

trans-unit.source: When overridden in a derived class, specifies the <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> object to use for namespace resolution.
trans-unit.target: Når overstyrt i en avledet klasse, angir du <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>objekt som skal brukes for navneområdet oppløsning.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>

trans-unit.source: Namespace resolution is supported using the <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> class which stores prefix and namespace Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) mappings.
trans-unit.target: Namespace oppløsning støttes ved bruk av den <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>klassen som lagrer prefikset og navneområdet Uniform URI (Resource Identifier)-tilordninger.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> requires namespace resolution, the prefix and namespace URI pair must be added to the <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> object and the SetContext method must be called to specify the <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> object to use for namespace resolution.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>krever navneområdet oppløsning, prefikset og navneområdet URI-par må legges til i <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>objekt og SetContext-metoden må kalles for å angi den <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>objekt som skal brukes for navneområdet oppløsning.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> </xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>

trans-unit.source: The following are important notes to consider when using the SetContext method.
trans-unit.target: Følgende er viktige hensyn å ta når du bruker SetContext-metoden.

trans-unit.source: - If the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> does not include a prefix, it is assumed that the namespace URI is the empty namespace.
trans-unit.target: -Hvis den <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>inneholder ikke et prefiks antas det at navneområde-URI er tom navneområdet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>

trans-unit.source: If your XML includes a default namespace, you must still use the SetContext method and provide an <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager> object that contains a prefix and namespace URI to handle the default namespace.
trans-unit.target: Hvis XML-filen inneholder et standard navneområde, må du fortsatt bruke metoden SetContext og angi en <xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>objekt som inneholder et prefiks og navneområde-URI til å håndtere standard navneområde.</xref:System.Xml.XmlNamespaceManager>

trans-unit.source: - You can also supply an <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver> object for namespace resolution to the <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.Compile%2A> method when you create your <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> object.
trans-unit.target: -Du kan også angi en <xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>for navneområdet løsningen til objekter i <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.Compile%2A>metoden når du oppretter din <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression>objektet.</xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.Compile%2A> </xref:System.Xml.IXmlNamespaceResolver>

trans-unit.source: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A> accepts <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltContext> as a namespace resolver, so you can implement a custom context and use functions and variables based on <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextFunction> and <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextVariable>.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A>godtar <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltContext>som et navneområde-Løsningsprogram, så du kan implementere en egendefinert kontekst og bruke funksjoner og variabler som er basert på <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextFunction>og <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextVariable>.</xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextVariable> </xref:System.Xml.Xsl.IXsltContextFunction> </xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltContext> </xref:System.Xml.XPath.XPathExpression.SetContext%2A>
